<br>
Currently when we send a pet against a mez'd mob, it gives us a message saying that it cannot wake the mob.  This is great, but if we want to save the enchanters life after mez breaks we basically have to chain nuke the mob to bring aggro onto ourselves, or pray the enchanter can kite the mob long enough after mez breaks for the pet to build up aggro.<br>
<br>
What if it was changed so that if the mob isn't on the pets hate list, the pet would add the mob into it's hate list with a &quot;Taunt Only&quot; flag, move into melee range and chain taunt the mob without engaging in melee?<br>
<br>
This is what warriors and other melees with taunt do now (if they're smart! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) before breaking mez when they have an Enchanter in their group.<br>
<br>
Here's an example of the above rule in action:<br>
1. Pet is engaged on a mob and the enchanter mez's the mob.<br>
2. Pet backs off with &quot;I cannot wake that mob master&quot; message and the mob is removed from the pets hate list.<br>
3. Mage targets the mob and issues /pet attack.<br>
4. Pet checks that the mob isn't on it's hate list then adds the mob to it's hate list with a Taunt Only flag and moves into melee range and chain taunts the mob.<br>
5. When mez breaks, the mob will whack the pet if he has built up enough taunt, and the pet would then remove the Taunt Only flag and engage as per normal pet rules.<br>
<br>
I've been thinking about this more lately in regards to PoP skills, with Enchanters (who are getting /pet attack), Necros, and now Magicians being able to mez, as it would make crowd control and pets more usefull and interesting.<br>
<br>
It doesn't take away from anyone elses abilities, it would mean pets could be used as a tool to assist enchanters and other mez'ers, and ads a new level of functionality to our roles.<br>
<br>
Just a thought, comments are welcome. <p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR=#FFFFFF FACE="Comic Sans MS, Sans-Serif, Courier New, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
