<br>
Ie: Two mobs come into camp, mage sets pet on one, other mob hits mage, enchanter mez's second mob.  When the pet has killed the first mob, it tries to switch to the other mob, and only THEN does it report &quot;I cannot wake that mob&quot;.  This would mean that under my previous theory, while the pet was still killing the first mob you wouldn't be able to /pet attack the second mob to set the pet up to taunt it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Change the rules to this:<br>
<br>
If the mob is on the pets hate list and the mob is mez'd, the pet moves the mob to the bottom of it's hate list and flags it as Taunt Only.<br>
<br>
Example 1:<br>
You to /pet attack a mez'd mob, and if that is the only mob on the pets hate list, it would move into position and taunt the mob.<br>
<br>
Example 2:<br>
Two mobs in camp, both on pets hate list, pet on one, second is mez'd.  When first dies, the pet moves into position on the second mez'd mob and begins to taunt.<br>
<br>
Example 3:<br>
5 mobs in camp, 2 active, 3 mez'd.  Pet kills it's current mob, and regardless of the aggro towards any of the mez'd mobs it will move to the other active mob to kill it first before approaching one of the mez'd mobs to begin taunting it.<br>
<br>
Under all of these situations, /pet back off will clear the pets hate list, including any Taunt Only entries.<br>
<br>
